  <h1>About</h1>

  <div class="wrapper">
    <p>Hi!</p>

    <p>I'm a <a href="/work">polyglot developer</a>, <a href="/work/illustration">illustrator</a> and <a href="/blog/thoughts/how-to-learn-drums">musician</a> with too many hobbies, a background in <a href="/blog/code-and-tech/magnetic-tapes-and-octal-dump-1">scientific research</a>, and a wide experience <a href="/about#I-love-travelling">working abroad</a> with multicultural teams.</p>

    <p>I started this blog more than a decade ago. There wasn't anything I wanted to achieve with it. I write for myself, about what I want, when I feel like it.</p>

    <p>I had a bunch of sites from the beginning of 2000 but I was never convinced about them. Around 2013-2014 I settled for the design and features you see now, and haven't updated it much since.</p>

    <p>You will find anything from posts about <a href="/blog/tags/git/">Git</a>, <a href="/blog/tags/python/">python</a>, <a href="/blog/tags/ruby/">ruby</a>, <a href="/blog/tags/bash/">Bash</a> or <a href="/blog/tags/html/">web development</a>, to reviews of <a href="/blog/thoughts/her">movies that I liked</a>. I may also swear from time to time, I hope you don't have issues with that.

  </div>

